<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="1587" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1587">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/75.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Vice Consul <persName type="to">Bevan</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>German Embassy transmits report that Constitutionalists have
                                confiscated warehouse and goods of German firm Eversbusch at
                                Tampico.</p>
                            <p>Investigate and if report correct, use good offices to secure release
                                of property.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>